n Eid sermon","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would go out on the days of Eid and lead the prayer. When the Prophet finished the prayer and invoked peace, he would stand and turn to people while they were sitting in their places of\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15686,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/14\/shorter-surahs-day-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":15425,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Shorter surahs in day, longer at dawn","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 14, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Samurah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would recite in the noon prayer, \u201cBy the night as it envelopes,\u201d (92:1) and similar chapters to those in the afternoon prayer, and in the morning prayer he would recite longer than those Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 459 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15427,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/28\/etiquette-adab-spread-peace\/","url_meta":{"origin":15425,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Salaam: Greeting groups with peace","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 28, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe rider should greet with peace those who are walking, those who are walking should greet those who are sitting, and a small group should greet a larger group.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6232, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2160\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":18516,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/03\/14\/prophet-siwak-wake-up\/","url_meta":{"origin":15425,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Miswak: The Prophet cleans his teeth after waking","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 14, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Hudhayfah reported: When the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, arose at night, he would clean his mouth with the toothstick. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 243, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 255 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062d\u064f\u0630\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0641\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064f \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3276,"url":"https:\/\/